{"cursor":"2911","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"Motion}} In parliamentary procedure, a 'motion' is a formal proposal by a member\nof a deliberative assembly that the assembly take certain action. In a parliament, this is also called a 'parliamentary motion'\nand includes legislative motions, budgetary motions, supplementary budgetary\nmotions, and petitionary motions. These can bring new business before the\nassembly or consist of numerous other proposals to take procedural steps or\ncarry out other actions relating either to a pending motion or the body itself.\n","linknr":189,"url":"Motion_(parliamentary_procedure)","recorded":1362667997,"links":15,"instances":["motion","parliamentary","election"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Motions|"],"headings":["Classification of motions","Proposing motions","See also","References"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["amend","motion"],["table","parliamentary"],["motion_and_amendment","election"]],"members":["amend","table","motion_and_amendment"],"related":["Parliamentary_procedure","Deliberative_assembly","Parliament","Legislative_motion","Budgetary_motion","Supplementary_budgetary_motion","Petitionary_motion","Robert's_Rules_of_Order","Main_motion","Subsidiary_motion","Incidental_motion","Privileged_motion","Motions_that_bring_a_matter_again_before_the_assembly","The_Standard_Code_of_Parliamentary_Procedure","Chairperson","Board_of_directors","Amend_(motion)","Cloture","Filibuster","Motion_to_recommit","Motion_of_no_confidence","Table_(parliamentary)","Private_member's_bill","Suspend_the_rules","Motion_and_amendment_(election)"]}